						<div class="postbody">Interesting, thanks for the replies.  That chibi-tech song (as much of an anti-fan I am of this person's work) is what I would imagine a &quot;no holds barred&quot; NES soundtrack would sound like, the 2A03 at it's full potential.  Problem with that, as tepples said, is that memory would be too expensive, and being able to store a bunch of different variations of the same note.  Then again, this is assuming for a functional NES game, so I'm assuming there would be severe compromises made to the game just to accommodate the music.  Sunsoft games were ridiculously small, and I'm guessing that's because all the space was used by the bassline samples.  Then there's also the issue with the 32K of dedicated music data...</div>

